<!-- ABSTRACT -->
<div class="page-break">
    <h2 class="center-text">ABSTRACT</h2>
    <p>The academic clearance process represents the final, critical milestone in a student's university journey. It is a multi-stakeholder procedure ensuring that a graduating candidate has satisfied all academic obligations, settled financial dues, and returned all institutional assets. However, in many developing higher education institutions, this process remains stubbornly analog and inefficient. Students are frequently required to physically navigate a bureaucratic maze, ferrying a "Clearance Form" from office to office—Registrar, Bursar, Librarian, Sports Department, and Head of Department—to obtain physical signatures and rubber stamps. This traditional method is prone to document loss, lacks transparency, creates significant "Graduation Anxiety" for students, and imposes a heavy administrative burden on faculty staff who must manually audit thousands of records.</p>
    <p>This project, titled <strong>"Degreefi,"</strong> facilitates the design and implementation of a centralized, web-based software solution to digitize and automate this workflow specifically for the Bachelor of Business Information and Communication Technology (BBICT) program. By leveraging the <strong>MERN Stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js)</strong>, the system shifts the institutional paradigm from manual verification to automated, algorithmic auditing.</p>
    <p>The core innovation of Degreefi is its robust <strong>"Eligibility Engine,"</strong> a backend logic layer that dynamically cross-references a student's entire academic history against the digitized Master Curriculum. This engine instantly computes the Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA), verifies credit loads, checks for core course completion, and identifies specific missing requirements (Gap Analysis) in real-time. The system provides a dual-interface ecosystem: a <strong>Student Dashboard</strong> for real-time progress monitoring, grade tracking, and digital document submission, and an <strong>Administrative Portal</strong> for the Registrar to oversee the entire cohort, verify uploaded proofs, and manage dynamic curriculum changes.</p>
    <p>The system architecture employs <strong>JSON Web Tokens (JWT)</strong> for secure, stateless authentication and utilizes a <strong>RESTful API</strong> design pattern to ensure horizontal scalability and ease of integration with future mobile platforms. Rigorous performance testing indicates that Degreefi significantly reduces the average clearance turnaround time from two weeks to approximately three business days, while simultaneously eliminating calculation errors in GPA auditing. This thesis documents the entire software development lifecycle (SDLC) of the project, from problem identification and theoretical framing (using General Systems Theory and TAM) to system design, implementation, and user acceptance testing.</p>
</div>

