    <h2>CHAPTER 2: LITERATURE REVIEW AND METHODOLOGY</h2>
    
    <h3>2.1 Theoretical Framework</h3>
    <h4>2.1.1 General Systems Theory (GST)</h4>
    <p>Proposed by Ludwig von Bertalanffy, GST posits that complex entities are formed by interacting parts. Degreefi acts as the <strong>Integration Layer</strong> for the university's subsystems (Academic, Financial, Logistics), harmonizing inputs (grades, receipts) into a decisive output (graduation clearance) via a feedback control loop.</p>
    <h4>2.1.2 Technology Acceptance Model (TAM)</h4>
    <p>TAM suggests adoption depends on <strong>Perceived Usefulness (PU)</strong> and <strong>Perceived Ease of Use (PEOU)</strong>. Degreefi maximizes PU via real-time tracking and PEOU via a user-friendly "Glassmorphism" interface.</p>

    <h3>2.2 Conceptual Framework</h3>
    <p>The framework maps Independent Variables (Automated Logic, Cloud Storage, Notifications) to Dependent Variables (Efficiency, Accuracy, Satisfaction, Transparency).</p>

    <h3>2.3 Technology Stack Justification</h3>
    <p>The <strong>MERN Stack</strong> was selected after rigorous analysis:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>MongoDB:</strong> Chosen for schema flexibility to handle nested curriculum structures and single-query performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Express.js & Node.js:</strong> Chosen for non-blocking I/O to handle concurrent file uploads without server crashes.</li>
        <li><strong>React.js:</strong> Chosen for the Virtual DOM's performance in updating real-time stats without page reloads.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.4 Software Development Methodology: Agile Scrum</h3>
    <p>The project used Agile Scrum with 2-week Sprints:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Sprint 0:</strong> Requirement Elicitation & Prototyping.</li>
        <li><strong>Sprint 1:</strong> Foundation & Authentication.</li>
        <li><strong>Sprint 2:</strong> Core Academic Tracking Logic.</li>
        <li><strong>Sprint 3:</strong> Documents Module (Multer).</li>
        <li><strong>Sprint 4:</strong> Admin Dashboard & UAT.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

