    <h2>CHAPTER 4: IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS</h2>
    
    <h3>4.1 Backend Implementation (The Eligibility Engine)</h3>
    <p>The engine, implemented in <code>studentController.js</code>, uses a 4-phase algorithm:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Context Retrieval:</strong> Fetches student records and master curriculum.</li>
        <li><strong>Pass Filter:</strong> Filters out failed/dropped courses.</li>
        <li><strong>Gap Analysis:</strong> Diffing algorithm identifies missing course codes.</li>
        <li><strong>Status Determination:</strong> Finite State Machine determines In Progress/Review/Ready status.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>4.2 File Upload Mechanism</h3>
    <p>Uses <strong>Multer</strong> middleware with a strict whitelist (JPG/PDF only) and timestamp-based renaming to prevent collisions and RCE attacks.</p>
</div>

